723700f-a.title: Manhattan: Vandam Street - Hudson Street
723700f-a.text:
99 to 81 Vandam Street, north side, west of, adioining, and
at Hudson Street. No. 97-93, the Thaddeus Davis Incorporated
Comgany plant, is to be sold at Receiver's Auction by Joseph P.
Day. No. 93-87 is a brand new annex of the Henry Heide candy
factory across the street, to which it is connected by a bridge.
It replaced four old four-story brick houses. The fifth house,
No. 85, was also demolished, and the space used for a service
drive. No. 83 is an old nine-story warehouse.
1924.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
